    <body>
        <div xml:id="NA399-kiḷavi">
            <p type="edition">1. itu neṭuṅ kālam vantoḻuka āṟṟāmai (ET: āṟṟāḷāy) vēṟupaṭa niṉṟa talaimakaḷait tōḻi “em perumāṉ itaṟkāya nallatu puriyum” eṉṟu talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākac colliyatu. 2. “itaṟkāya nallatu puriyum perumāṉ tiṟam vēṇṭum” eṉṟāṭkut talaimakaḷ colliyatūumām.</p>
            <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is how the confidante said to HER who stood [there] when she underwent changes on account of [her] inability to bear it when [HE] kept coming for a long time, when HE was behind the fence: “our great man will do good for it’s sake.” 2. It is also what SHE said to her who said “it is necessary for the great man to do good for it’s sake.”</p>
            </div>
      <div xml:id="NA399">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aruvi yārkkum peruvarai yaṭukkattuk</l>
<l>            kuruti yoppiṉ kamaḻpūṅ kāntaḷ</l>
<l>            variyaṇic ciṟakiṉ vaṇṭuṇa malarum</l>
<l>            vāḻaiyañ cilampiṟ kēḻal keṇṭiya</l>
<l>            nilavarai nivanta palavuṟu tirumaṇi</l>
<l>            yoḷitikaḻ viḷakkat tīṉṟa maṭappiṭi</l>
<l>            kaḷiṟupuṟaṅ kāppak kaṉṟoṭu vatiyu</l>
<l>            māmalai nāṭa ṉayantaṉaṉ varūum</l>
<l>            perumai yuṭaiya ḷeṉpatu</l>
<l>            tarumō tōḻiniṉ ṟirunutaṟ kaviṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            The man from a land of big mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent">            where the youthful elephant cow,</l>
<l rend="indent">            who gave birth in the brightly glittering light</l>
<l rend="indent2">            of the brilliant sapphires that are many, come up on the field border</l>
<l rend="indent2">            dug up by the boar on the plantain mountain side,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            where the Malabar lily in fragrant flowers resembling blood</l>
<l rend="indent3">            blossoms for the bees with wings [and] adorned with stripes to eat</l>
<l rend="indent4">            on the side of the big mountain, where the waterfall roars,</l>
<l rend="indent">            resides with [her] calf, while the bull stands guard,</l>
<l rend="indent4">             has begun to long [for you]. When he comes,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nayantaṉaṉ varūum</term>: how to account for syntax here? Tradition, to be sure, reads a <term xml:lang="ta">muṟṟeccam</term> here.</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">            will [his] saying</l>
<l rend="indent2">            “she possesses greatness”</l>
<l>        give [back], friend, your brilliant forehead’s beauty?</l>
            </lg>
      </div>
